The paper deals with problems related to communications and cryptography, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses algorithmic techniques and their performance, which are relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the decoding of multiple-input multiple-output systems, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes practical variants of embedding decoding, which may involve machine learning techniques, and hence may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
